               <head>Persian letter addressed to Jacob Bosanquet</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Murāsilah</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100074 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85104368 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009117611 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115489" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4229-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Large letter or murāsilah lacking any seal, header, or invocation addressed to <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_306130428" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/nr89009806" role="rcp">Jacob Bosanquet</persName> , noting the departure of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_24503113" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/nr96043659" role="subject">Sir Harford Jones, Baronet</persName> (Sar Harfurd Juns Bārūnat ṣāḥib Bahādur)
following the signing of a treaty 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                        <p>Cropped and mounted 
</p>
                        <p>IOL stamp: 23 Nov 1926
</p>
                        <p>English translation (IO Islamic 4230) refer to the letter ending with a seal that is not present, indicating the letter has been cropped and is not in its original condition
</p>
                        <p>Seals on reverse, Isa al-Husayni 1218 repeated twice</p>
                     </note>
